narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: My understanding and knowledge of saxophone performance reached the next level. I see where to go next and know that I have not attained it yet, but feel that with the guidance given in this course I have a clear way forward.
they are lessons so how to play your instrument
I learned to sing in a different style which was cool.
Healthy ways to play cello (methods to reduce strain in shoulder, especially); musicality; confidence in performance

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: This course was great for individual feedback on saxophone performance and general improvement. This course would be better if moved to the canvas or classes v2 website

I was extremely excited to begin lessons. In the first lesson, my teacher talked too much and didn't let me sing enough. When I asked him what to practice he said singing in your normal daily life was enough. This was disappointing. Also I had to keep reaching out to him to get lessons. He was slow to respond and it began taking more and more energy to chase after him to send me songs and to schedule lessons. He also structured lessons around warm ups instead of around singing music. This was disappointing.
Strength: enjoyed the studio classes; gave us a chance to hear/critique our peers' playing and to be exposed to a variety of styles Weakness: none

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: I would recommend this course to anyone wanting to gain valuable insight and feedback into how to improve their performance.
Make sure you get a good teacher for voice lessons. Make clear that you want to have a regular time for your lessons and that unless explicitly noted, both people should be there.
